Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: formatclass
Version: 0.0.12
Summary: formatclass(cls,...) - format class representation
Home-page: https://github.com/russianidiot/formatclass.py
Author: UNKNOWN
Author-email: UNKNOWN
License: UNKNOWN
Description: .. README generated with readmemako.py (github.com/russianidiot/readme-mako.py) and .README dotfiles (github.com/russianidiot-dotfiles/.README)
        
        Install
        ```````
        
        :code:`[sudo] pip install formatclass`
        
        Usage
        `````
        
        .. code:: python
        
        	>>> from formatclass import formatclass
        	
        	>>> formatclass(cls)
        
        Example
        ```````
        
        .. code:: python
        
        	>>> class Cls(object): pass
        	>>> class Cls2(Cls): 
        	    def __init__(self,arg,arg2="default"): pass
        	
        	# default
        	>>> formatclass(CLS2)
        	'Cls2(__main__.Cls)(arg, arg2="default")'
        	
        	# args - False/True (default True)
        	>>> formatclass(CLS2,args=False)
        	'Cls2(__main__.Cls)'
        	
        	# fullname - False/True (default True)
        	>>> formatclass(CLS2,fullname=False)
        	'Cls2(Cls)(arg, arg2="default")'
        
